  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesize that by monitoring and analyzing physiological parameters
      (heart rate, blood pressure, saturation) and well-being (pain, nausea, vomiting, comfort) the
      SMART ANGEL ™ device improves the quality of care after major or intermediate outpatient
      surgery. This active surveillance will result in a decrease in the rate of unplanned recourse
      (hospitalization, consultation, telephone call).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
